=head1 NAME

procdiff -- Visualization tool for two different Tcl procedure implementations.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

procdiff [-help] [-w] <procedure> <file1> <file2>

procdiff [-help] [-w] <file1> <file2> <procedure>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Given a Tcl procedure name and two files containing implementations of that procedure, procdiff allows you to compare and visualize both implementations in isolation.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over

=item B<-h>

Print the command's usage string or this man page

=item B<-w>

Ignore whitespace differences


=back

